{
  "stem": "27509.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But I am not quite sure-- I can't put an exact date on it, whether it was 14, or 14 and 1/2, or whatever it is.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But that was the time of the break, in terms-- and he knew that the gap between us is-- is widening.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And then, at Shabbat table, we used to argue about the Jewish religion, and Jewish mannerisms, and God.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And yes, there is a God.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "No, there isn't a God, and all the things that my generation's people were facing, facing the one generation before them argued, as some people probably do today, but maybe much more understandably so, being more exposed to TV, and to literature, and so on.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "In those days, one had to be more-- more rebellious by nature to take on your own father with respect, respectfully.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But yet, at the same time, to agree to disagree, so to speak, in terms of such fundamentals, because we didn't talk about trivia-- we talked about the most fundamental issue in our very existence and so on.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But I would have never, never dreamed of speaking-- of using a world of dubious quality or respect in addressing my father or my mother.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "It was always with the utmost respect.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "It was so ingrained and it was so part of the culture of-- the nature-- the issue of [NON-ENGLISH], the respect-- respect your father and your mother, that it was almost like with your mother's milk, you had it.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And it is-- it was inconceivable that-- today you hear children speak to their parents.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "It is-- I just-- I can't-- by now, yeah, I'm used to it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But in the beginning, it was just, just-- I couldn't adjust to it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I can't adjust to it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that was it.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
